LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 271, As Amended in the Senate
BY STATE AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO ADVERTISING ILLEGAL DRUGS; AMENDING TITLE 18, IDAHO CODE, BY THE
3 ADDITION OF A NEW CHAPTER 90, TITLE 18, IDAHO CODE, TO PROHIBIT THE AD-
4 VERTISING OF ILLEGAL DRUGS, TO PROVIDE A PENALTY, AND TO DEFINE A TERM;
5 AMENDING SECTION 19-4705, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE FOR THE APPORTIONMENT
6 OF CERTAIN FINES; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY.
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
8 SECTION 1. That Title 18, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby amended
9 by the addition thereto of a NEW CHAPTER, to be known and designated as Chap-
10 ter 90, Title 18, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
11 CHAPTER 90
12 ADVERTISING ILLEGAL DRUGS
13 18-9001. ADVERTISING ILLEGAL DRUGS PROHIBITED. (1) Any person who
14 willfully publishes any commercial advertisement, in any medium, within the
15 state of Idaho for marijuana, narcotics, or other psychoactive substances
16 that are illegal under Idaho Code and illegal under the laws of the juris-
17 diction where the marijuana, narcotics, or other psychoactive substances
18 are provided, including federal, state, or local laws, is guilty of a mis-
19 demeanor, punishable in accordance with section 18-113, Idaho Code, with a
20 fine of five hundred dollars ($500) to be imposed for each violation. Each
21 day in which a violation of this section exists shall be considered a sepa-
22 rate offense.
23 (2) As used in this section, "commercial advertisement" means an ad-
24 vertisement that encourages consumers to engage with products or services to
25 benefit a commercial enterprise.
26 SECTION 2. That Section 19-4705, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
27 amended to read as follows:
28 19-4705. PAYMENT OF FINES AND FORFEITURES -- SATISFACTION OF JUDGMENT
29 -- DISPOSITION -- APPORTIONMENT. (1) Except as otherwise provided in subsec-
30 tion (2) of this section:
31 (a) All fines and forfeitures collected pursuant to the judgment of
32 any court of the state shall be remitted to the court in which the judg-
33 ment was rendered. The judgment shall then be satisfied by entry in the
34 docket of the court. The clerk of the court shall daily remit all fines
35 and forfeitures to the county auditor, who shall at the end of each month
36 apportion the proceeds according to the provisions of this chapter.
37 Other existing laws regarding the disposition of fines and forfeitures
38 are hereby repealed to the extent such laws are inconsistent with the
39 provisions of this chapter, except as provided in section 49-1013(5),
40 Idaho Code.

